Step 1: Create the custom prompt FIRST
Go to make.powerautomate.com → AI Hub → Prompts → Build your own prompt (or in the left nav, find AI Hub/Prompts).
In the prompt builder:
Prompt name: EMS Import Assessment
Prompt instructions (type this in the prompt text area):
You are an AI assistant for a GRC Evidence Management System that monitors monthly data imports from RSA Archer (controls) and LeanIX (applications). In a healthy environment, month-over-month changes are minimal. Reference Controls rarely change. Business Processes are very stable. Control Procedures may have 1-5 new per quarter. Applications change slowly, 1-3 new per quarter. Any removal is significant. Multiple evidence-affecting changes in one import is unusual. Analyze the import results provided and give a 2-3 sentence assessment. Start with NORMAL, REVIEW, or UNUSUAL. Flag any anomalies and suggest actions if needed.
Add one input variable: Click + Add input (or the insert input button)

Input name: ImportResults
Sample data: Reference Controls: 0 new, 10 updated, 0 removed. Business Processes: 0 new, 19 updated, 0 removed. Control Procedures: 1 new, 0 updated, 0 removed. Applications: 0 new, 0 updated, 0 decommissioned.

Make sure the input variable ImportResults is referenced in the prompt text. Add it at the end of the instructions:
Here are the import results to analyze: [ImportResults]
Test the prompt in the builder by clicking Test. Verify it returns a sensible assessment.
Save the prompt.
Step 2: Use the prompt in the flow
Go back to your flow. Delete the current AI Import Assessment action if you added one. Add a new action:

AI Builder → Run a prompt
In the Prompt dropdown, select EMS Import Assessment (the one you just created)
The ImportResults input field will appear. Click fx:

concat('Reference Controls: ', string(variables('varRCNew')), ' new, ', string(variables('varRCUpdated')), ' updated, ', string(variables('varRCRemoved')), ' removed. Business Processes: ', string(variables('varBPNew')), ' new, ', string(variables('varBPUpdated')), ' updated, ', string(variables('varBPRemoved')), ' removed. Control Procedures: ', string(variables('varCPNew')), ' new, ', string(variables('varCPUpdated')), ' updated (evidence-affecting), ', string(variables('varCPRemoved')), ' removed. Applications: ', string(variables('varAppNew')), ' new, ', string(variables('varAppUpdated')), ' updated (evidence-affecting), ', string(variables('varAppDecom')), ' decommissioned.')

Rename to: AI Import Assessment

Step 3: Store the result
After AI Import Assessment, add Dataverse → Update a row:

Table: Import Cycles
Row ID — fx: variables('varImportCycleID')
AI Assessment field: use lightning bolt → select Text from the AI Import Assessment output
Rename to: Save AI Assessment

